The subprogram - early child development. The program aims to stimulate the development and support the social integration of children with developmental delay risk and children with disabilities, strengthening a child and family, and preventing disability and abandonment. Component of providing with wheelchairs to and supporting employment of the persons with disabilities. Under the state program, these persons are entitled to:

•        Mechanic Wheelchair;
•        Electric Wheelchair;
•        Walking stick for the blind;
•        Walking cranes / crutches;
•         Crutches
•        Rolling frame (walker);
•         Prosthetic and Orthopedic Means;
•         Hearing Device;
•        Cochlear implant.

Do you require a wheelchair or prosthetic-orthopedic treatment? Any individual (citizen of Georgia) with disabilities, according to the needs, can get a voucher rom a social service agency in order to obtain prosthetic-orthopedic device or a wheelchair

Note: the basis for rejection on the auxiliary means (except orthosis)  is if warranty period of the similar means, received in previous years by under the state program, is not expired. The program providing crutches, canes, walking sticks for the blind and walking frames. The program aims  to improve the quality of  functional independence of the target group  and facilitate the process of their integration into society. Subprogram for facilitating communication of deaf people. The task of the program is to support social integration of the target group.

